pe.";i:32;s:83:"These steps are all done for the sake of safety and should be considered necessary.";i:33;s:75:"Once done using your user manual for the opener locate the adjustment bolt.";i:34;s:53:"This bolt will have nuts on either side of it and is.";i:35;s:109:"Some garage doors use a chain attached to a ceiling-mounted electric motor to open and close the garage door.";i:36;s:83:"Over time the constant rotation of the rocket that drives the chain along with the.";i:37;s:175:"How To Replace A Garage Door Opener Drive Chain And Cable Assembly Garage Door Won T Open Or Close Force Adjustments You Craftsman Series 100 Garage Door Opener With Two 3 On.";i:38;s:56:"Installation procedures may vary according to door type.";i:39;s:92:"While inside your garage close the door and mark the vertical centerline of the garage door.";i:40;s:59:"Extend the line onto the header wall above the door spring.";i:41;s:45:"Open the door to the highest point of travel.";i:42;s:71:"Mark a line on the header wall 2 5cm above the highest point of travel.";i:43;s:43:"Using the wall button open the garage door.";i:44;s:77:"Locate the curved open limit adjustment slot on the back of the opener motor.";i:45;s:91:"Insert a screw driver into the adjustment screw and turn the screw clockwise for more open.";i:46;s:49:"Travel and counterclockwise for less open travel.";i:47;s:48:"This is for minor adjustment to the open travel.";i:48;s:63:"We are installing a genie garage door opener on a wayne dalton.";i:49;s:74:"We are installing a genie garage door opener on a wayne dalton steel door.";i:50;s:70:"We are to the point where we connect the L shaped bracket to the door.";i:51;s:54:"The door already has a bracket installed but it is on.";i:52;s:31:"If Your Garage Door is Binding.";i:53;s:60:"Here are the steps to follow if your garage door is binding.";i:54;s:85:"Using a screwdriver loosen the screws which hold the tracks in the garage door frame.";i:55;s:105:"Now you can align the track so it is